result.name: Iron Cow Taiwanese Beef Noodles

reviews.text:
Taiwan cuisine is hot in Hong Kong these days. We got many Taiwanese noodle shops and dumpling shops in the town all of a sudden. 

This restaurant is a simple and quick style Taiwanese noodle shop. I can't stop admiring the noodle whenever I dropped at here. The noodle texture is very unique and the soup tastes very Taiwanese and good.

And even more, I would declare without any hesitation that its afternoon tea set is the best choice at the same cost around the area. 

Staffs are busy and shows a very average manner of HK restaurant. If they stay bright and kind, it can be the happiest place for all.
Good taste. However pork and wine, both available. Nice service. Good atmosphere.

Noodles 4/5
Bubble tea 4/5
Soup in soup noodles 3/5
Service 1/5
Value 3/5 

Would come again if it were cheaper, but food lacked that something special to make it an 80hkd bowl of soup noodles. Unpleasant service also wouldn't draw me back.

Loved it. The food was perfect, the prices totally fair and the atmosphere nice. You get your time with the menu, write down your order, pay and then all you have to do is enjoy your meal and leave afterwards without any waiting or queueing.
We chose this place as it offers small dishes and bubble teas both hot & cold. The fried sweet potatoes taste awesome as it comes with sweet & sour plum powder.
